Building a simple website using HTML and CSS is a great way to start learning web development. Below is a step-by-step tutorial that will guide you through the process.

### Step 1: Set Up Your Development Environment

1. **Install Text Editor**: Choose a code editor to write your HTML and CSS. Popular options include:
   - Visual Studio Code
   - Sublime Text
   - Atom
   - Notepad++ (Windows)

2. **Set Up a Project Folder**: Create a folder on your computer where you will store your website files. Name it something like `MyWebsite`.

### Step 2: Create HTML File

1. **Create a New File**: Inside your project folder, create a new file and name it `index.html`.

2. **Basic HTML Structure**: Open `index.html` in your text editor and add the following basic HTML boilerplate code:

   ```html
   <!DOCTYPE html>
   <html lang="en">
   <head>
       <meta charset="UTF-8">
       <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
       <title>My Simple Website</title>
       <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
   </head>
   <body>
       <header>
           <h1>Welcome to My Simple Website</h1>
       </header>
       <nav>
           <ul>
               <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
               <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
               <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
           </ul>
       </nav>
       <main>
           <section id="home">
               <h2>Home Section</h2>
               <p>This is the home section of the website.</p>
           </section>
           <section id="about">
               <h2>About Section</h2>
               <p>This section contains information about the website.</p>
           </section>
           <section id="contact">
               <h2>Contact Section</h2>
               <p>Contact us at email@example.com.</p>
           </section>
       </main>
       <footer>
           <p>&copy; 2023 My Simple Website</p>
       </footer>
   </body>
   </html>
   ```

### Step 3: Create CSS File

1. **Create a New File**: In the same project folder, create a new file, and name it `styles.css`.

2. **Basic CSS Styles**: Open `styles.css` and add the following CSS code to style your website:

   ```css
   body {
       font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
       line-height: 1.6;
       margin: 0;
       padding: 0;
   }

   header {
       background: #007BFF;
       color: white;
       padding: 20px;
       text-align: center;
   }

   nav {
       background: #333;
       color: white;
       padding: 15px;
       text-align: center;
   }

   nav ul {
       list-style: none;
       padding: 0;
   }

   nav a {
       color: white;
       text-decoration: none;
       margin: 0 15px;
   }

   main {
       padding: 20px;
   }

   section {
       margin-bottom: 20px;
       padding: 15px;
       border: 1px solid #ccc;
       border-radius: 5px;
   }

   footer {
       text-align: center;
       padding: 15px;
       background: #333;
       color: white;
       position: relative;
       bottom: 0;
       width: 100%;
   }
   ```

### Step 4: View Your Website

1. **Open HTML File in Browser**: After saving both files, open `index.html` in a web browser. You can do this by right-clicking the file and selecting "Open with" followed by your preferred browser.

2. **Check Your Design**: Ensure that your website displays correctly and styles are applied as expected.

### Step 5: Make Changes and Experiment

- Feel free to make changes to the HTML and CSS files to see how they affect your website.
- Try adding more sections, changing colors, or experimenting with different fonts.

### Step 6: Expand Your Knowledge

To further enhance your website, consider the following:

- **Learn JavaScript**: Adding interactivity to your website.
- **Responsive Design**: Use media queries in CSS to make your site mobile-friendly.
- **Web Hosting**: Research how to host your website so that it can be accessed online (e.g., GitHub Pages, Netlify).

### Step 7: Publish Your Website

1. **Choose a Hosting Service**: After developing your website, choose a hosting service.
2. **Upload Your Files**: Follow the instructions provided by the hosting service to upload your `index.html` and `styles.css` files.

Congratulations! You have built and potentially published your first simple website using HTML and CSS. Continue learning and experimenting, and you’ll be able to create even more complex and feature-rich websites!

